						<summary>

						<p>On the fourth face of the fourth pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Tyāgarāja shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 25: 931-32 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This records the gift of sheep by the <hi rend="italic">Nāṭṭār</hi> of Umbaḷa-nāḍu for a perpetual lamp to the god Tirumaṟaikkāḍu-uḍaiyār.</p>						

